parameters: "No good, I can't get in touch with Tina."

"Maybe she's in a place where the communication spell
doesn't reach? Didn't she say she was going into a cave
yesterday?"

"If that's the case, she might be staying inside the cave to
conduct her investigation."

The communication device sends out spells to connect
communication, similar to radio waves. As Rise said, it may
not work inside caves.

In addition, if the monsters inside the cave are irregular,
as Rise mentioned, it's possible that she's staying inside
to continue her investigation.

What Rise says makes sense. Since Tina went there, the
likelihood of what Rise suggested is higher.
"But I have a bad feeling about this."
"Hey, don't say scary things like that!!"

"It's definitely concerning that we haven't heard from
Tina."

"But if we rush in there on a hunch and end up finding
nothing, we'd just alert Maroges to our strategy and that
would be counterproductive."

"I understand how you feel, but we sent Tina in there
because she's an overwhelming force."

"There's hardly anything Tina can't handle, and while I
understand the anxiety, let's wait for the three-week
period."
"Right, Tina Onee-san will surely be fine."

(I know this precisely because I've seen Tina Onee-san in
action all this time. There's no way she would lose.)
Three weeks had passed since Tina took on the request.
